Instead of putting the live network sniffer inside our IDS analysis loop—which would create a massive bottleneck—we decouple them completely using our new best friend, Redis.

We build a dedicated, lightweight sniffer.py that does nothing but pull packets from the wire and push them directly into a raw Redis list acting as a high-speed FIFO queue (packet_buffer).

Our existing main.py gets re-armed to run as a worker pool, continuously popping raw packets from that Redis list, analyzing them through the signature/ML layers, and publishing alerts.


